================================================================================
REVIEWED SUMMARY
================================================================================

C++ header:         include/emTreeDump/emTreeDumpControlPanel.h
C++ implementation: src/emTreeDump/emTreeDumpControlPanel.cpp

Purpose: emRasterGroup subclass serving as the control-panel widget
for the in-app TreeDump viewer. Displays the node's Commands as
clickable buttons (RunCommand(index)) that launch external programs
with the node's args, scoped to the node's directory. Surfaces the
Commands / Files arrays of the displayed emTreeDumpRec as an
interactive toolbar.

Status: NOT PORTED — in-app dump-renderer subsystem out of scope for
the current dump-producer work (Phase 1 of
docs/superpowers/specs/2026-04-24-treedump-port-design.md).

Only meaningful as the control panel for emTreeDumpRecPanel; with no
RecPanel in the Rust port, there is nothing to host this control
widget.

Rust equivalent for now: none.

Future port path: ports together with emTreeDumpRecPanel. Depends on
emRasterGroup (toolkit widget) and a command-launching facility
equivalent to C++'s process-exec path.
